1. color ⭐⭐⭐

Used to change the text color.

Syntax
color: red;
Example
<p class="one">Hello World</p>
.one{
    color: blue;
}

Output

🔵 Hello World

Different Ways
Color Name
color: red;
Hex Code
color: #ff0000;
RGB
color: rgb(255,0,0);
RGBA (with transparency)
color: rgba(255,0,0,0.5);
2. font-size ⭐⭐⭐

Changes the size of text.

font-size: 20px;
Example
<p class="size">CSS Learning</p>
.size{
    font-size:30px;
}

Output:

Large text

Common Units
font-size:16px;
font-size:2em;
font-size:1.5rem;
font-size:150%;

For beginners, px is the easiest to use.

3. font-family ⭐⭐⭐

Changes the font style.

font-family: Arial;
Example
p{
    font-family: Arial;
}
Multiple Fonts (Best Practice)
font-family: Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;

If Arial isn't available, the browser uses Helvetica.

Font Categories
font-family: serif;
font-family: sans-serif;
font-family: monospace;
font-family: cursive;
font-family: fantasy;
4. font-weight ⭐⭐⭐

Controls how bold the text is.

font-weight:bold;
Example
p{
    font-weight:bold;
}

Output:

Bold Text

Numeric Values
font-weight:100;
font-weight:300;
font-weight:400; /* Normal */
font-weight:700; /* Bold */
font-weight:900;
5. text-align ⭐⭐⭐

Aligns text horizontally.

Left
text-align:left;
Center
text-align:center;
Right
text-align:right;
Justify
text-align:justify;
Example
<h1>Welcome</h1>
h1{
    text-align:center;
}

Output:

        Welcome
6. text-transform ⭐⭐⭐

Changes the capitalization.

Uppercase
text-transform:uppercase;

Output

HELLO WORLD
Lowercase
text-transform:lowercase;

Output

hello world
Capitalize
text-transform:capitalize;

Output

Hello World
Example
p{
    text-transform:uppercase;
}
7. text-decoration ⭐⭐⭐

Adds or removes decorations.

Underline
text-decoration:underline;

Output

<u>Hello</u>

Overline
text-decoration:overline;
Line Through
text-decoration:line-through;

Output

Hello

Remove Underline from Links
<a href="#">Home</a>
a{
    text-decoration:none;
}
8. line-height ⭐⭐⭐

Controls the space between lines.

Without line-height:

Hello
World
CSS

With

line-height:40px;

There will be more vertical spacing.

Example
p{
    line-height:35px;
}

Useful for paragraphs.

9. letter-spacing ⭐⭐⭐

Controls spacing between letters.

letter-spacing:5px;

Output

H E L L O
Example
h1{
    letter-spacing:8px;
}
Complete Example
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
<style>

h1{
    color:blue;
    font-size:40px;
    font-family:Arial, sans-serif;
    font-weight:bold;
    text-align:center;
    text-transform:uppercase;
    text-decoration:underline;
    letter-spacing:5px;
}

p{
    color:gray;
    font-size:18px;
    line-height:30px;
    text-align:justify;
}

a{
    text-decoration:none;
    color:red;
}

</style>
</head>

<body>

<h1>CSS Tutorial</h1>

<p>
CSS makes web pages beautiful.
It controls colors, fonts, spacing,
alignment and much more.
</p>

<a href="#">Click Here</a>

</body>
</html>
Interview Questions
1. What is the difference between font-weight: bold and font-weight: 700?

They are generally equivalent for most fonts. bold is a keyword, while 700 is the numeric value. Numeric values provide finer control when a font supports multiple weights.

2. What is the difference between text-transform and text-decoration?
text-transform	text-decoration
Changes the case of text (uppercase, lowercase, capitalize).	Adds visual decoration like underline, overline, or line-through.
3. How do you remove the underline from a hyperlink?
a{
    text-decoration:none;
}
4. What does line-height do?

It controls the vertical spacing between lines of text, improving readability.

5. What does letter-spacing do?

It increases or decreases the spacing between individual characters.

